.TH HYPRIDLE 1 "2025-10-03" "hypridle 0.1.7" "Hyprland Ecosystem"
.SH NAME
hypridle \- Hyprland's idle management daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hypridle
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hypridle
is an idle management daemon for the Hyprland ecosystem.
It uses the ext\-idle\-notify\-v1 Wayland protocol to detect user inactivity
and execute configurable actions after specified timeouts.
.PP
Features include support for D\-Bus loginctl commands (lock, unlock,
before\-sleep), D\-Bus idle inhibit (used by applications such as Firefox and
Steam), and systemd idle inhibitors.
.PP
A configuration file is required;
.B hypridle
will not start without one.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config " " \fIpath\fR
Specify a custom configuration file path.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose logging.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress all output except errors.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Show version information.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is searched for at
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/hypr/hypridle.conf ,
.IR ~/.config/hypr/hypridle.conf ,
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_DIRS/hypr/hypridle.conf ,
and
.IR /etc/hypr/hypridle.conf .
.SS General section
.TP
.B lock_cmd
Command to run on D\-Bus lock event. Default: empty.
.TP
.B unlock_cmd
Command to run on D\-Bus unlock event. Default: empty.
.TP
.B before_sleep_cmd
Command to run on D\-Bus prepare_sleep event. Default: empty.
.TP
.B after_sleep_cmd
Command to run after the system wakes from sleep. Default: empty.
.TP
.B ignore_dbus_inhibit
Ignore D\-Bus\-sent idle inhibit events. Default: false.
.TP
.B ignore_systemd_inhibit
Ignore systemd\-inhibit idle inhibitors. Default: false.
.SS Listener section (repeatable)
.TP
.B timeout
Timeout duration in seconds before executing on\-timeout. Required.
.TP
.B on\-timeout
Command to execute when the timeout is reached.
.TP
.B on\-resume
Command to execute when activity resumes after a timeout.
.SH EXAMPLES
Typical configuration to lock screen and suspend:
.PP
.nf
general {
    lock_cmd = hyprlock
    before_sleep_cmd = loginctl lock\-session
}

listener {
    timeout = 300
    on\-timeout = loginctl lock\-session
}

listener {
    timeout = 600
    on\-timeout = systemctl suspend
}
.fi
.SH SYSTEMD INTEGRATION
.B hypridle
ships with a systemd user service:
.PP
.RS
.B systemctl \-\-user enable \-\-now hypridle.service
.RE
.PP
Alternatively, add to
.IR hyprland.conf :
.PP
.RS
.B exec\-once = hypridle
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR hyprlock (1),
.BR Hyprland (1),
.BR hyprctl (1)
.SH AUTHOR
The Hyprland Development Team
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at
.UR https://github.com/hyprwm/hypridle/issues
.UE .
